ratings.comment: Almost always late for class. When you have a question to ask and he doesn't know the answer, he answers the question in a way that no one can understand. Not helpful. Recommended to stay away from his discussion.

David is an excellent TA.  Dif Eq isn't the most difficult course, but it is a challenge.  David took the time to type up notes several times and even held weekly problem solving sessions to go over homework problems outside of discussion section.  Collected homework and graded based on completion.  Wasn't the most organized, but tolerable.Laid bac

Good Guy and even better TA. This is one of the only TAs you will find that is easy to understand, has easy to understand lectures, and is very helpful. If you do the homework before class, like assigned, you will hit this class out of the park and get an easy A.

Nice but not a great teacher.  Always made mistakes on the board or didn't know how to do problems.  Seemed really behind what the other TA's were doing, especially with section grading.  He was always late to class, really scatter-brained, and just flat out annoying.  I would switch sections.
